						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/S-T-Policy/EU-agricultural-S-T-dialogue/Related-developments/SCRI-support-for-farmers-in-Malawi" title="SCRI support for farmers in Malawi" alt="link">SCRI support for farmers in Malawi</a></h2>

	
					<p>The Scottish Government's International Development fund has provided an award of nearly £400,000 to farmers in Malawi to improve their potato crops and to benefit from the expertise of researchers from the Scottish Crops Research Institute (SCRI). The Institute in collaboration with the International Potato Center and national potato researchers will work with farmers to combat constraints and improve potato crop yields that would eventually reduce poverty and increase food security in Malawi. (Source: CBU, 26 March 2010)</p>
							<p><span class="date">26/04/2010</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/Dossiers/S-T-Policy/EU-agricultural-S-T-dialogue/Related-developments/SCRI-support-for-farmers-in-Malawi">Read more...</a>
</div>
<br class="cl">
</div>
</p>
						
						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/S-T-Policy/EU-agricultural-S-T-dialogue/Related-developments/Germany-to-fund-food-security-projects" title="Germany to fund food security projects" alt="link">Germany to fund food security projects</a></h2>

	
					<p>The German government has provided more than US$6 million to fund five FAO projects aimed at strengthening the food security of smallholders in developing countries. One of the projects is global in scope and aims at improving the abilities of regional organizations to develop, implement, and monitor food security training programs. A second project helps small farmers to enter into business partnerships with small and medium agricultural enterprises in Kenya and promote business-oriented planning and management capacity. A third project, targeted at Sierra Leone, Uganda and Tanzania, assists district administrators to improve the preparation, implementation and monitoring of local plans that are compliant with ‘the right to food’ policies. The projects will be implemented between 2010 and 2012. (Source: FAO Media Center, 10 March 2010)</p>
							<p><span class="date">22/03/2010</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/Dossiers/S-T-Policy/EU-agricultural-S-T-dialogue/Related-developments/Germany-to-fund-food-security-projects">Read more...</a>
</div>
<br class="cl">
</div>
