						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="document" href="/Dossiers/S-T-Policy/EU-agricultural-S-T-dialogue/Related-developments/Conclusions-of-stakeholders-conference-Africa-Europe-Cooperation-in-S-T-Mombasa-November-2009" title="Conclusions of stakeholders’ conference ‘Africa-Europe Cooperation in S&amp;T’, Mombasa, November 2009" alt="document">Conclusions of stakeholders’ conference ‘Africa-Europe Cooperation in S&amp;T’, Mombasa, November 2009</a></h2>

	
	
	
	
					<p>








 




  
  

	
	<a href="/var/knowledge/storage/images/media/images/castnet/295325-1-eng-GB/castnet.jpg" rel="lightbox[]" >	
	  </a>
	
		
			
	
  	






	 
  





	On the 10 and 11 November 2009 a stakeholders' conference entitled ‘Africa-Europe Cooperation in Science and Technology: Status and Way Forward’ was held in Mombasa, Kenya as an activity of the CAAST-Net project (http://www.caast-net.org), funded by the European Union's 7th Framework Programme for Research and Technological Development. The conference was organized by the Kenyan Ministry of Higher Education, Science and Technology (MoHEST) in collaboration with the International Bureau of the German Federal Ministry of Education and Research (IB of BMBF). Its goal was to enhance bi-regional cooperation in science and technology (S&amp;T) through an examination of the nature and the role of cooperation processes. The link below contains the ‘Summary Report and Recommendations’ (in English and French), which are the result of intensive discussions at the conference and which have been prepared in consultation with conference participants and therefore represent a consensus of opinion of a substantial body of stakeholders. </p>
							<p><span class="date">23/02/2010</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="document" href="/Dossiers/S-T-Policy/EU-agricultural-S-T-dialogue/Related-developments/Conclusions-of-stakeholders-conference-Africa-Europe-Cooperation-in-S-T-Mombasa-November-2009">Read more...</a>
</div>
<br class="cl">
</div>
</p>
						
						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/S-T-Policy/EU-agricultural-S-T-dialogue/Related-developments/Dialogue-between-Europe-and-its-Southern-partners-on-agricultural-research-and-climate-change" title="Dialogue between Europe and its Southern partners on agricultural research and climate change" alt="link">Dialogue between Europe and its Southern partners on agricultural research and climate change</a></h2>

	
					<p>As part of its European geo-scientific strategy, CIRAD is working with partners to organize an international conference in Brussels on 16 and 17 December 2009, entitled &quot;Dialogue Between Europe and its Southern Partners on Agricultural Research and Climate Change&quot;. Over the last couple of years, significant progress has been made in terms of improved coordination and cooperation between European national programmes in agricultural research through SCAR (Standing Committee on Agricultural Research) and through EIARD (European Initiative for Agricultural Research for Development) and, more recently, ERA-ARD (an EC FP6-funded project). The conference will focus on three major themes: What are the challenges and why a dialogue between Europe and its Southern partners is necessary? ; Mapping of agricultural research programmes related to climate change in Europe ; Priorities for the future: What are the agricultural research priorities and what partnerships to build to adapt agriculture to climate change and to mitigate the impacts? What could be the agenda of a European joint programme initiative in this field? 120 key policy-makers and research experts in the fields of agriculture, research and international cooperation, members of ERA-ARD, SCAR, EIARD and partners from Southern countries are expected at the conference. (Source: CIRAD, 26 November 2009)</p>
							<p><span class="date">8/12/2009</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/Dossiers/S-T-Policy/EU-agricultural-S-T-dialogue/Related-developments/Dialogue-between-Europe-and-its-Southern-partners-on-agricultural-research-and-climate-change">Read more...</a>
</div>
<br class="cl">
</div>
</p>
						
						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/S-T-Policy/EU-agricultural-S-T-dialogue/Related-developments/EU-launches-digital-library" title="EU launches digital library " alt="link">EU launches digital library </a></h2>

	
					<p>The EU has launched a digital library that offers documents dating to nearly 60 years ago, in 23 languages. All documents ever edited on behalf of EU institutions, agencies and other bodies will be available in the library. The electronic library is free to individuals, companies and libraries worldwide, which can download documents as PDF files. About 12 million pages (roughly 110,000 EU publications) are available for download. (Source: CNN.com/technology, 20 October 2009)</p>
							<p><span class="date">4/11/2009</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/Dossiers/S-T-Policy/EU-agricultural-S-T-dialogue/Related-developments/EU-launches-digital-library">Read more...</a>
</div>
<br class="cl">
</div>
</p>
						
						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/S-T-Policy/EU-agricultural-S-T-dialogue/Related-developments/EU-FP7-Calls-for-Proposals-2009" title="EU FP7 Calls for Proposals 2009" alt="link">EU FP7 Calls for Proposals 2009</a></h2>

	
					<p>The Seventh Framework Programme for Research and Technological Development (FP7) is the EU's main instrument for funding research in Europe. It runs over the period 2007-2013, with a total budget of over € 50 billion. This money will (for the most part) be spent on grants to research actors all over Europe and beyond, in order to co-finance research, technological development and demonstration projects. On July 30th 2009, 53 calls for proposals have been launched in various areas of research, including:


'Health';

'Food, agriculture and fisheries, and biotechnology';

'Information and communication technologies';

'Nanosciences, nanotechnologies, materials and new production technologies';

'Energy';

'Environment (including climate change)';

'Transport';

'Socio-economic sciences and humanities';

'Space';

'Security'


All calls can be consulted and application documents accessed at CORDIS website via the link below.</p>
							<p><span class="date">10/08/2009</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/Dossiers/S-T-Policy/EU-agricultural-S-T-dialogue/Related-developments/EU-FP7-Calls-for-Proposals-2009">Read more...</a>
</div>
<br class="cl">
</div>
</p>
						
						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/S-T-Policy/EU-agricultural-S-T-dialogue/Related-developments/EU-Call-for-Proposals-2009-Global-Programme-on-Agricultural-Research-for-Development-ARD" title="EU Call for Proposals 2009 - Global Programme on Agricultural Research for Development (ARD)" alt="link">EU Call for Proposals 2009 - Global Programme on Agricultural Research for Development (ARD)</a></h2>

	
					<p>In the context of the <a href="http://ec.europa.eu/europeaid/what/food-security/index_en.htm" target="_blank">EU Food Security Thematic Programme</a> (FSTP) an open call for proposals has been launched. The present action is specifically related to the FSTP component &quot;Supporting the delivery of international public goods contributing to food security: research and technology&quot;, and is targeting global public goods in the field of agricultural research. The overall objective of the programme is agricultural innovation for smallholder farmers in developing countries for food security, in the context of impact and adaptation to climate change and in favour of economic development.Proposals should address one of the six priorities of the programme, which include conservation agriculture in dry land areas, innovation systems involving traditional knowledge, market access, risk management, agricultural diversification and control of endemic livestock diseases and zoonoses. <i>Deadline for submission of applications is 6 November 2009</i>. Detailed information on this call for proposals can be found in the document Guidelines for Grant Applicants, accessible via the link below.</p>
							<p><span class="date">23/07/2009</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/Dossiers/S-T-Policy/EU-agricultural-S-T-dialogue/Related-developments/EU-Call-for-Proposals-2009-Global-Programme-on-Agricultural-Research-for-Development-ARD">Read more...</a>
</div>
<br class="cl">
</div>
</p>
											</div> 	
	<br class="cl" />
<p>

